Actor Uche Oputa has expressed sadness over his father’s continuous stay in the den of kidnappers The actor few weeks ago cried out his father Kenneth Oputa had been kidnapped The distraught son in an emotional video appealed for the safe return of his father   Jide Kene speaks on caucus in Nollywood     Anticipate my new single Pemi Samba, says Lobor     ManiX, TesKi launch indie label with Rock with me   He said: “Today is the third Friday my father was abducted alongside his friend, Rapheal Ojukwu. My father Kenneth Oduputa from my village in Amoebu Ebeanato osu local government of Imo state. “We have still not found him. We still haven’t spoken to him. “He has still not been released. Please let’s continue praying until something happens. “Join me in praying for my father and for his safe return and safe release from the hand of his abductors. Thank you and God bless you.”